# Walkthrough - Troy Snow Cleaning Notification App

I have created a notification application to check the snow cleaning status for the City of Troy, MI.

## Components

1.  **Web Application ([index.html](file:///Users/I808883/.gemini/antigravity/brain/e32ba253-8e99-4635-9848-02b00fb21049/index.html))**: A user-friendly interface to check status and get browser notifications. Built with TypeScript.
2.  **Python Script ([check_snow_status.py](file:///Users/I808883/.gemini/antigravity/brain/e32ba253-8e99-4635-9848-02b00fb21049/check_snow_status.py))**: A command-line tool for checking status and getting desktop notifications.

## How to Use

### Web Application
1.  **Compile TypeScript**:
    ```bash
    npm install
    npx tsc
    ```
2.  Open [index.html](file:///Users/I808883/.gemini/antigravity/brain/e32ba253-8e99-4635-9848-02b00fb21049/index.html) in your web browser.
3.  Enter your **Section Number** (e.g., 14).
4.  Click **Check Status** to see the current status.
4.  Click **Notify Me** to start monitoring. The app will check every minute and send a browser notification when the status becomes "COMPLETED".
    *   *Note: You must allow browser notifications when prompted.*

### Python Script
You can run the script from your terminal.

**Check status once:**
```bash
python3 check_snow_status.py --section 14
```

**Monitor status (polls every 60 seconds):**
```bash
python3 check_snow_status.py --section 14 --poll 60
```
*   The script will send a desktop notification when the section is completed.
*   Press `Ctrl+C` to stop monitoring.

